      • getUnit

        public int getUnit()
        Get the unit which is setting to peripheral. It is binary value.

        TNTUnitNone(=000(2)):unit is none
        TNTUnitKilogram(=001(2)):kg
        TNTUnitPound(=010(2)):lb
        TNTUnitStPound(=100(2)):st-lb

        Returns:
        mUnit The unit of measure.

      • getStepsDistinctionLevel

        public int getStepsDistinctionLevel()
        Get the steps distinction level (default:5).

        Range:0 - 19 (20 - 255 is reserved value）
        notice:In case of setting value as out of above range, the peripheral automatically set min or max value

        This property means sensitivity of detecting steps.
        The higher value is set, the easier device counts steps.
        We don't recommend to change this value since end-user doesn't know the device's sensitivity .

        Returns:
        The steps distinction level.

      • setStepsDistinctionLevel

        public void setStepsDistinctionLevel(int level)
        Set the steps distinction level (default:5).

        Range:0 - 19 (20 - 255 is reserved value）
        notice:In case of setting value as out of above range, the peripheral automatically set min or max value

        This property means sensitivity of detecting steps.
        The higher value is set, the easier device counts steps.
        We don't recommend to change this value since end-user doesn't know the device's sensitivity .
